decks.notes: The main concept of this deck is to control the game by utilizing a combination of counterspells, removal spells, and card draw. By using cards like Fatal Push, Counterspell, and Force of Negation, the deck aims to disrupt the opponent's strategy and prevent them from gaining too much advantage. Additionally, cards like Relic of Progenitus and Psychic Frog help in maintaining card advantage and controlling the graveyard. The deck also includes powerful creatures like Ketramose, the New Dawn and LÃ³rien Revealed to close out the game once the opponent's resources are depleted.

The deck revolves around utilizing cards like Spelunking, Amulet of Vigor, and Primeval Titan to quickly assemble a powerful board state and mana base. By leveraging the combination of land tutors, mana ramp, and utility lands like Valakut, the Molten Pinnacle and Lotus Field, the deck aims to create explosive turns where it can overwhelm opponents with large creatures and powerful spells. The main goal is to set up a winning combo involving lands and creatures such as Arboreal Grazer and Dryad of the Ilysian Grove to secure victory.

The deck focuses on using a combination of control and aggressive tactics to disrupt the opponent's strategy while building up your own board presence. By using cards like Thoughtseize to disrupt their hand and Fatal Push to remove key threats, you can pave the way for your powerful creatures like Sheoldred, the Apocalypse and Boggart Trawler to dominate the battlefield. Relic of Progenitus and Necrodominance provide additional ways to control the board while Soul Spike can be used as a finisher. Overall, this deck aims to outvalue and outpace the opponent in order to secure victory.

This deck focuses on quickly filling up the graveyard with cards like Burning Inquiry, Goblin Lore, and Faithless Looting to enable powerful early plays like Hollow One and Vengevine. Marauding Mako and Detective's Phoenix can apply pressure while also providing value through their abilities. Fear of Missing Out can serve as a finisher when the opponent is low on resources. The deck aims to be fast and aggressive, utilizing the graveyard as a resource to overwhelm the opponent before they can stabilize.
